etymologies: early 20th century; earliest use found in Science. From phyto- + -saur, after either scientific Latin Phytosauria, suborder name or scientific Latin Phytosaurus, genus name, so called on account of the supposition at the time that the animals were herbivorous

definitions: A crocodile-like reptile of the Late Triassic suborder Phytosauria.

notes.text: Formerly used only of the genus Phytosaurus.
